    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Unanswered Questions About T.W.A. Flight 800</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tony Molloy letter on Christine Negroni's July 16 essay holds true cause of crash of TWA Flight 800 might have come to light sooner if news media and FBI had not focused on bomb and missile theory (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Four years after the Flight 800 disaster, Christine Negroni [''The Real 'Secret' of Flight 800,'' Opinion, July 16] sees fit to lay the blame for misleading the public about the real cause to conspiracy theorists.</p>
        <p>In reality, had CNN and other news media, and an overzealous F.B.I., not focused only on the bomb and missile theory -- while neglecting the possibility of mechanical error -- the true cause might have come to light a lot sooner.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Four years after the Flight 800 disaster, Christine Negroni [''The Real 'Secret' of Flight 800,'' Opinion, July 16] sees fit to lay the blame for misleading the public about the real cause to conspiracy theorists.</p>
        <p>In reality, had CNN and other news media, and an overzealous F.B.I., not focused only on the bomb and missile theory -- while neglecting the possibility of mechanical error -- the true cause might have come to light a lot sooner.</p>
        <p>Had Ms. Negroni, who covered the crash for CNN, and other journalists been less sensational and more level-headed four years ago, the conspiracy promoters might have had a harder time.</p>
        <p>TONY MOLLOY  Rocky Point</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
